oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: American topographical map of vicinity near Metz and Moselle River
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Lt. James J. Coghlan's map shows the area around Moselle village of Preny. Scrawled note across reads in part "Here took out first raiding party and went into town of Preny captured a corporal of 153rd German Infantry [and] killed one, night of Oct. 12, 1918." At the top are instructions for recovery and return of unit property. On back of map is a standard message form for use in calling for artillery or infantry support. Coghlan served in the 55th Inf. Regt.
